        "body": "Hey, found a few things worth fixing while going through the code.\n### Portability\nsystem(\"clear\") only works on macOS/Linux — on Windows the screen just doesn't clear. Same with afplay in playSound(), that's a macOS-only binary. On any other OS the sound silently does nothing, which is fine, but worth knowing.\nSigned/unsigned comparison warning\nThe loop in drawMaze compares a signed int against maze.size() which returns size_t. Most compilers will warn about this. \n### Quick fix:\n### for (int i = 0; i < (int)maze.size(); i++)\nPLAYER constant is never used\nPLAYER is defined at the top but the actual emoji is just hardcoded inline in drawMaze. Either use the constant or drop the definition.\ncin has no EOF guard\nIf input ends unexpectedly (e.g. piped input), the loop spins forever. Adding if (!cin) break; after the read would handle it.\nMinor: 'S' tile is never cleared\nThe start cell stays as 'S' the whole game. Not a visible bug since the player sprite overrides it, but it's a bit inconsistent if anything ever reads that cell.\n\n\n\n## works fyn on macOS (the afplay/clear stuff works fine here, just flagging it for anyone on other platforms!)🤙🏿",
